# video / revideo

Full **Revideo** (headless Motion Canvas fork) — agent writes all scenes in
`out/src/`. The step script scaffolds project config and copies voice assets; it
never overwrites existing `src/`. Render is fully headless via `renderVideo()` /
`npm run render` — no browser-UI click needed.

controls do
  video.title: { label: "Project id", type: "text" }
  video.duration: { label: "Duration hint (seconds)", type: "text" }
  video.fps: { label: "FPS hint", type: "select", options: "24, 30, 60" }
end

## Required reading

- [Revideo docs](https://docs.re.video/) — official docs (llms reference)
- [midrender/revideo](https://github.com/midrender/revideo) — MIT source + examples
- Authoring API is largely shared with Motion Canvas (`makeScene2D`, `makeProject`, signals, tweening)

## Voiceover

Chain `audio/tts-local` first. WAV lands in `public/voice/voice.wav`; sync via the
`Audio` tag in your scene.

## Render

```bash
# scaffold once (step script does this), then write src/project.ts + scenes
npm install
node render.mjs            # headless: renderVideo({projectFile:'./src/project.ts'})
# or:
npm run render             # CLI render
```

## Failure modes

- **ffmpeg missing** — `brew install ffmpeg` if the bundled binary isn't used
- **Chromium not fetched** — puppeteer downloads it on `npm install`; re-run install if absent
- **Empty src/** — agent must write `src/project.ts` + scenes; see `out/REVIDEO.md`
- **Re-run preserves src/** — step will not clobber agent-authored TS
- **Telemetry** — set `DISABLE_TELEMETRY=true` in agent/CI envs
